      }
    ],
    "http://ogp.me/ns#title": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "Marina Orsini | performing her debut album Reconstruire les saisons |  Thu, May 28, 2026, 7:30 pm | Babs Asper Theatre"
      }
    ],
    "http://ogp.me/ns#image": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "https://naccnaca-eventimages.s3.amazonaws.com/40093/untitled_design__large.png"
      }
    ],
    "http://ogp.me/ns#description": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "Marina Orsini revealed her talent for songwriting with her debut album, Reconstruire les saisons, which is deeply rooted in the Francophone song tradition. Released in February 2025 to critical acclaim, the album was an instant hit, topping the French-language iTunes sales charts and ranking first in Canadian sales that same week. The album is the result of valuable collaborations with producer, composer and pianist Catherine Major, lyricists Jeff Moran and Nelson Minville, and fellow singer–songwriters Paul Piché, Richard Séguin and Manue  Tadros, with each of whom Marina performs a sublime duet. \n\nEncouraged by this enthusiastic reception, the actor, host, author and performer,..."
      }
    ],
